        * tools/rapidjson:

          Converting IDL data types to/from JSON requires special codegen

          Problem
          -------

          The existing approach to converting an IDL datatype to/from JSON
          is
          based on code generated by the IDL compiler that is specific to
          the
          JSON conversion.

          Solution
          --------

          Define the ValueReader interface and a JsonValueReader
          implementation.
          (ValueWriter and JsonValueWriter already existed.)  The
          ValueReader/ValueWriter interfaces present a generic interface
          for
          deserializers/serializers. The IDL compiler has the responsiblity
          of
          define generic procedures that use these interfaces to populate a
          value (vread) or recite a value (vwrite).

          This change creates a number of short-term and long-term
          opportunities:

          1. The rapidjson pass can be removed from the IDL compiler.

          2. The v8 pass can be removed by implementing ValueReader and
          ValueWriter for the v8 environment. Presumably, these
          implementations
          would reside in node-opendds repository.

          3. Support for CDR/XCDR (de)serialization can be converted to the
          ValueReader/ValueWriter interfaces.

          4. (3) supposes manual implemenations of vread and vwrite for
          type
          objects and type identifiers. These would correspond to the
          existing
          serializer support.

          4. A C++ ValueWriter implementation can be defined and used to
          generate C++ code that re-creates a value. This could be used to
          great effect in the type object pass to generate the type object
          and
          type identifier output.

          5. JsonValueWriter could be applied to type objects and type
          identifiers to create an IDL to JSON pass to replace ITL. Json
          schema
          support may be interesting to consider as well.

